@startuml
title Intent mandatory profile proposal

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #424242
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #424242

rectangle "TMF921 Intent\nbase resource model" as TMF #EEF2FF

rectangle "Intent management entity\nmandatory profile\n\nTMF-aligned, not TMF-minimal" as PROFILE #E8F5E9

TMF --> PROFILE : intent management entity conformance\ndefines runtime Intent profile

rectangle "External write contract" as WRITE #FFF3E0 {
  rectangle "External consumers may supply\n\n- consumer-owned Intent content\n- submit request-control field\n\nExternal consumers must NOT supply\nlifecycleStatus in create, PUT, PATCH,\nor any other external write request body." as WRITE_CONTRACT

  rectangle "submit semantics\n\n- omitted on initial create = submit=true\n- submit=false = save / keep Draft\n- submit=true = request admission\n- omitted on existing Draft = remain Draft" as SUBMIT
}

rectangle "Draft authoring state" as DRAFT #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "Minimal Draft create\n\n- name\n- submit = false\n- @type\n- @baseType\n\nStrongly recommended:\n- humanExpression" as DRAFT_CREATE

  rectangle "Draft editability\n\nAll attributes accepted by the\nPUT / PATCH request contract\nare mutable while Draft.\n\nid is immutable.\nlifecycleStatus is not writable." as DRAFT_EDIT

  rectangle "Draft is not runtime-active\n\n- not admitted\n- not optimised\n- not assured\n- not sent to change execution\n- does not drive activeVersion" as DRAFT_NON_RUNTIME
}

rectangle "Admission gate" as GATE #FFE0B2 {
  rectangle "Admission requires\n\n- name\n- expression\n- expression.@type\n- expression.iri\n- expression.expressionValue\n- @type\n- @baseType\n\nStrongly recommended:\n- humanExpression\n- intentSpecification.id" as ADMISSION_PROFILE

  rectangle "If admission is accepted\n\nIntent management entity assigns:\n- lifecycleStatus = Acknowledged\n- statusReason\n- statusChangeDate\n- version\n\nExternal consumer does not assign lifecycle." as ASSIGN_STATUS
}

note top of GATE
Terminology:
submit=true is the consumer action.
admission is IC MS processing.
Acknowledged is the first lifecycle state
when admission is accepted.

There is no Submitted lifecycle state.
end note

rectangle "IntentSpecification resolution" as RESOLUTION #E3F2FD {
  rectangle "If intentSpecification.id supplied\n\n- authoritative\n- must reference ACTIVE spec\n- must align with expression.iri" as SPEC_ID_SUPPLIED

  rectangle "If intentSpecification.id omitted\n\nResolve ACTIVE IntentSpecification\nusing expression.iri" as SPEC_ID_OMITTED

  rectangle "Reject if\n\n- zero ACTIVE matches\n- multiple ACTIVE matches\n- supplied id conflicts with iri" as REJECT_RESOLUTION
}

rectangle "Persisted Intent" as PERSISTED #E0F2F1 {
  rectangle "Mandatory persisted response\n\n- id\n- href\n- name\n- version\n- lifecycleStatus\n- statusReason\n- statusChangeDate\n- intentSpecification.id\n- expression\n- expression.@type\n- expression.iri\n- expression.expressionValue\n- @type\n- @baseType" as PERSISTED_MIN

  rectangle "lifecycleStatus is read-only\nfor external consumers\n\nIt is assigned, transitioned,\nand projected by the\nintent management entity." as LIFECYCLE_READONLY
}

rectangle "Non-Draft version change" as CHANGE #F3E5F5 {
  rectangle "Once Intent leaves Draft\n\ngeneral PUT / PATCH attribute\nupdate on that version is not allowed.\n\nMaterial changes require:\ncreate new Draft version -> edit -> submit=true" as MATERIAL_CHANGE

  rectangle "activeVersion\n\nDraft versions do not drive activeVersion.\n\nactiveVersion points to the version\ndriving the external lifecycle projection." as ACTIVE_VERSION
}

PROFILE --> WRITE : defines external write behaviour
WRITE --> DRAFT : submit=false
WRITE --> GATE : submit=true or omitted on initial create
DRAFT --> DRAFT_EDIT : PUT / PATCH while Draft
DRAFT --> GATE : later submit=true
GATE --> RESOLUTION : resolve governing specification
RESOLUTION --> PERSISTED : exactly one valid ACTIVE contract
RESOLUTION -[#red,dashed]-> WRITE : reject resolution or admission failure
PERSISTED --> CHANGE : after leaving Draft
CHANGE --> DRAFT : material change requires\nnew Draft version

note right of WRITE_CONTRACT
The key rule is broad:
lifecycleStatus must not appear
in any external write request body.

This covers create, PUT, PATCH,
and any other write operation.
end note

note right of SUBMIT
submit is an approved extension
request-control field.

It is not a lifecycle field.
end note

note bottom of DRAFT_EDIT
Draft is editable, but only through
the accepted request contract.

Response/projection fields are not
client-supplied writable fields.
end note

note bottom of PERSISTED
intentSpecification.id may be omitted
by the submit request when expression.iri
resolves unambiguously.

After admission, the persisted Intent
records the resolved specification id.
end note

note bottom of ACTIVE_VERSION
Avoid ambiguous pointer names:
- effectiveVersion
- currentVersion

Use activeVersion.
end note

@enduml
